full_text: Factors Contributing To Geographic Variation In End-Of-Life Expenditures For #Cancer Patients https://t.co/WwBZq0CDnE

Results from a prospective, multiregional study published in @Health_Affairs find that geographic variation in end-of-life expenditures could be associated with availability of services and physician-reported beliefs. #EndofLifeCare #HealthSpending https://t.co/n5vwfbY256
Factors Contributing To Geographic Variation In End-Of-Life Expenditures For Cancer Patients | Health Affairs https://t.co/IlyrEvz0vb

Variations in end-of-life care (for cancer patients) is a greater reflection of physicians' preferences and attitudes than patients' values: https://t.co/enALtDUx85. Even if data is ten years old, physician attitudes driving end-of-life care over patient preferences is concerning

Interesting research investigating factors contributing to variation In end-of-life care for patients with #cancer. https://t.co/sDqxaeorYe @ASCO @Health_Affairs @DanaFarber #GeriOnc #PallOnc @CostsofCare https://t.co/ujfgtZgkMv
